@Joshua I realize this to be a misleading headline because the sum of these groups could easily put a county over the 0.5% minimum.  However, I never would have guessed it to be this low for most US counties for Chinese and Indian Asian Americans even though I live in a rural area with Americans of predominantly European descendants.  

Another burning question for me would be: what would the map look like if all the Asian Americans were combined?  Would combining the numbers bring many more counties to the 0.5% minimum or just unseen data to the already counties highlighted?

And still another question (which will hopefully be answered in the Reveal) is: How many counties meet the criterion and how many do not?
